dfischer.utils

Class PerformanceData

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.PerformanceData

  • public class PerformanceData
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains all measured performance data of a test run.

    The abstact basis class HttpLoadTest holds during the execution of a load test program a single object reference to this class.
    The measured data of all URL calls are collected with the methods setPassed() and setFailed().

    At the end of the load test program all data - including all dependent references - are written to disk as binary file (*.prxres) by using the method writeObjectToFile() .

    Later, the binary file (*.prxres) can readed back into a new instance of this class by using the method readObjectFromFile().

    See Also:
    HttpLoadTest.performanceData, setPassed(int, dfischer.utils.HttpTestURL), setFailed(int, java.lang.String, dfischer.utils.HttpTestURL, dfischer.utils.LogVector), writeObjectToFile(java.lang.String), readObjectFromFile(dfischer.utils.SymmetricEncryptContext, java.lang.String)

               int percentileUrlSamplingRateAddOption)
        Crates an initializes a new instance of a measurement result for TEST_RESULT_TYPE_HTTP_NORMAL and TEST_RESULT_TYPE_PURE_JUNIT.
        Creates internal an array of PerformanceDataRecord[maxPageBreaks + maxUrlCalls].
        Parameters:
        maxPageBreaks - number of page breaks per loop
        maxUrlCalls - number of URL calls per loop
        parallelUsers - planned number of concurrent users
        maxParallelThreadsPerUser - planned number of max. parallel URL calls per user. -1 = all URL calls are executed in serial order
        maxTestDuration - planned test duration in seconds. 0 = unlimited
        loopsPerUser - planned number of loops per user. 0 = unlimited
        httpProtocolVersion - applied HTTP protocol version ("1.0" or "1.1").
        startupDelay - startup delay in milliseconds of concurrent users
        requestTimeout - request timeout in seconds per single URL call.
        samplingInterval - Statistic sampling interval in seconds during test execution.
        percentilePageSamplingRate - Additional sampling rate per web page call in percent (0..100%)
        percentileUrlSamplingRate - Additional sampling rate per url call in percent (0..100%)
